************************
SUMMARY OF DATA FILES
************************

1. List of data files
	Filename: Climate Normal 1980-2010
	Short description: Climate Normals on indicators like Mean Temperature, Maximum Temperature, Minimum Temperature and Precipitation

	Filename: Merged Monthly Weather Summary for 2014, 2017,2018
	Short description: Merged data for weather summary for 2014, 2017, 2018. Dataset tracks total precipitation, no of days where precipitation were over the specified level, for temperature the 
	average, departure from the average and highest value on those average. The average is for mean, max and min temperatures. These data are for different stations and is on monthly basis.	

	Filename: Monthly Weather Summary 2014
	Short description: Merged data for weather summary for 2014. Dataset tracks total precipitation, no of days where precipitation were over the specified level, for temperature the 
	average, departure from the average and highest value on those average. The average is for mean, max and min temperatures. These data are for different stations and is on monthly basis.
	
	Filename: Monthly Weather Summary 2017-2018
	Short description: Merged data for weather summary for 2017 and 2018. Dataset tracks total precipitation, no of days where precipitation were over the specified level, for temperature the 
	average, departure from the average and highest value on those average. The average is for mean, max and min temperatures. These data are for different stations and is on monthly basis.
	Note: The dataset is not available for all months.

2. Relationships between files
	Merged Monthly Weather Summary for 2014, 2017,2018 is the merged dataset of two datasets, Monthly Weather Summary 2014 and Monthly Weather Summary 2017-2018 respectively.	


